   ▀ ▄ STATEMENT NOTES                                                    ▀▄
 ▄▄▀                                                                       ▐██▄
███ Well well, we somehow knew that the scene isn't really ready for a      ███
███ release like this, but when you look at it, there isn't any news to it. ███
███                                                                         ███
███ Quantum Break uses streaming videos for it's live action sequences.     ███
███ That means that you have to allow game to access internet access - the  ███
███ same way you in some games can access multiplayer or LAN access.        ███
███                                                                         ███
███ Furthermore, even if you wont allow cracked material to allow internet  ███
███ access, you will get a "unable to steam" message screen, with a "skip   ███
███ this episode" button and you can continue to play the game offline.     ███
███                                                                         ███
███ We're sure that eventually someone will come up with a "streaming movie ███
███ patch", but expect it to be really huge in size. Only the XBOX ONE got  ███
███ access to those live movie sequences offline - and the size of those    ███
███ are over 76GB, but the PC does not have access to such a feature.       ███
███ Therefore the game isn't incomplete, as those live sequences can still  ███
███ be access in online mode or skipable in offline mode.                   ███
███                                                                         ███
███ So nukers - another pointless nuke!                                     ███
███                                                                         ███
